<p>coma refers especially to beautifully done-up hair of women.</p>
<p>caesaries refers to the properly done-up hair of males.</p>
<p>pilus is a count noun, as opposed to all the others which are mass nouns, and the word typically refers to short hair or bristles, particularly on animals.</p>
